</para>-->
<para id="fs-id1164566867037">Air is pumped into a car tire, causing its temperature to increase. In another tire, the temperature increase is due to exposure to the sun. Is it possible to tell what caused the temperature increase in each tire? Explain your answer.</para>
<list id="fs-id1164561361067" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-alpha">
<item>No, because it is a chemical change, and the cause of that change does not matter; the final state of both systems are the same.</item>
<item>Although the final state of each system is identical, the source is different in each case.</item>
<item>No, because the changes in energy for both systems are the same, and the cause of that change does not matter; the state of each system is identical.</item>
<item>Yes, the changes in the energy for both systems are the same, but the causes of that change are different, so the states of each system are not identical.</item>
</list>
