<para id="fs-id1164562026439">Two distinct systems have the same amount of stored internal energy. Five hundred joules are added by heat to the first system, and 300 J are added by heat to the second system. What will be the change in internal energy of the first system if it does 200 J of work? How much work will the second system have to do in order to have the same internal energy?</para>
<list id="fs-id1164566871866" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-alpha">
<item>700 J; 0 J</item>
<item>300 J; 300 J</item>
<item>700 J; 300 J</item>
<item>300 J; 0 J</item>
</list>
</problem>
